FAQs
What are the eligibility criteria for studying at Universidad Europea?

Applicants must have completed their secondary education and meet the specific requirements of their chosen program. Proficiency in English or Spanish is also required, depending on the language of instruction.

How much does it cost to study at Universidad Europea?

Tuition fees vary by program and level of study, averaging between €10,000 to €20,000 per year. Living expenses typically range from €700 to €1,200 per month.

Are there scholarships available for international students?

Yes, Universidad Europea offers various scholarships based on academic merit, financial need, and specific talents. Additionally, the Spanish government and private organizations provide scholarship opportunities.

What is the application process for Universidad Europea?

The application process involves submitting an online application through the university’s portal, along with academic transcripts, a personal statement, letters of recommendation, and proof of language proficiency.

Can international students work while studying in Spain?

Yes, international students in Spain are allowed to work part-time during their studies and full-time during holidays, providing an opportunity to gain work experience and support their living expenses.
